[According to the most recent WHO Influenza Update, released on 15 Jul
2011,
http://www.who.int/csr/disease/influenza/latest_update_GIP_surveillance/en/index.html,
in Australia, the [southern hemisphere influenza] season appeared to
have started with notable increases in influenza-like illness (ILI)
consultations and confirmed cases. The most common virus detected
nationally in Australia was influenza A(H1N1)2009, though this is not
consistent in every state.

This report indicates that Queensland is particularly badly affected
and that the predominant virus is probably the influenza A/(H1N1) 2009
strain.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Australian state of
Queensland can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/008N. -
Mod.CP]
